The students supervise the activities of the children or youth group aplying the knowledge acquired in the creative activities module.

The guidelines for the practice can be found  munder the link "Õppematerjalid" (Study Materials).Objectives/eesmärkid:  Supervising the children/youth group in a practice environment the student receives an adequate notion about him-/herself as a supervisor. The student has perfectioned his/her understanding about the role of creativity in learning/teaching and on practical techniques supporting creativity in different levels (individuaal, study and work environment). The student's competencies in consciously applying creativity in education have increased.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student  - has an overview of different methods of developing creativity and is able to apply them; - knows how to apply different principles of creating learning environments that develop and support creativity; - is able to see the peculiarities in creativity of each child/youth and develop it with suitable methods; - knows the main group processes, can lead a youth group, supervised to be able to find a suitable communication styles, can work in a team; -is able to plan, carry out, analyse and evaluate his/her activities during the practice.
